'''David Douděra''' (born 31 May 1998) is a Czech professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[right midfielder]] for [[Czech First League]] side [[SK Slavia Prague|Slavia Prague]] and the [[Czech Republic national football team|Czech Republic national team]].

==Club career==

===Dukla Prague===
Douděra joined [[FK Dukla Prague]] at the age of 15. After good appearances for [[FK Dukla Prague|Dukla Prague]]'s B-team, he got his official debut for the club in a [[Czech First League]] against [[SK Sigma Olomouc|Sigma Olomouc]] on 29 September 2017. Douděra started on the bench, but replaced [[Róbert Kovaľ]] in the 62nd minute.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Sigma Olomouc 3-0 Dukla Prague|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2017/09/23/czech-republic/czech-liga/sk-sigma-olomouc/ac-dukla-praha/2472381/|website=Soccerway|date=23 September 2017}}</ref> He played 10 games further in the 2017–18 season, five as a starter and the rest from the bench. In the following season, Douděra became a regular starter with 30 league appearances; 21 of them as a starter. However, Dukla was relegated to the [[Czech National Football League]] for the 2019–20 season.

===Mladá Boleslav===
In the winter break of the 2019–20 season, Douděra transferred from Dukla to [[FK Mladá Boleslav|Mladá Boleslav]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Douděra: Pořád si připadám, jako bych byl v Realu Madrid|url=https://boleslavsky.denik.cz/fotbal-prvni-liga/doudera-porad-si-pripadam-jako-bych-byl-v-realu-madrid-20200131.html|publisher=[[Deník]]|date=31 January 2020|language=cs|access-date=30 April 2024}}</ref> He debuted for the team on 14 February 2020 against [[SK Dynamo České Budějovice|Dynamo České Budějovice]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=České Budějovice 3-0 Mladá Boleslav|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2020/02/14/czech-republic/czech-liga/sk-dynamo-ceske-budejovice/fk-mlada-boleslav/3036953/|website=Soccerway|date=14 February 2020}}</ref> In the [[2021–22 Czech First League]], Douděra scored 10 goals and registered 4 assists for Boleslav in 31 matches.<ref name="signedslavia">{{cite web|url=https://www.idnes.cz/fotbal/prvni-liga/david-doudera-prestup-slavia-mlada-boleslav.A220525_194547_fotbal_ten|title=Slavia má první posilu, Douděra jde naplnit rodinný osud|language=cs|work=iDNES|date=25 May 2022|access-date=30 April 2024}}</ref>

===Slavia Prague===
Following the end of the 2021–22 Czech First League, Douděra became the first summer signing for [[SK Slavia Prague|Slavia Prague]].<ref name="signedslavia"/> He made his competitive debut for the club in a 4–0 away win against Gibraltarian side [[St Joseph's F.C.|St Joseph's]] in the second qualifying round of the [[2022–23 UEFA Europa Conference League]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.idnes.cz/fotbal/pohary/david-doudera-slavia-gibraltar-st-joseph-s-2-predkolo-konferencni-liga.A220721_231830_fot_pohary_jic|title=Poprvé s hvězdou na srdci. Byl to zážitek, vyprávěl slávista Douděra|language=cs|work=iDNES|date=22 July 2022|access-date=30 April 2024}}</ref> On 9 May 2026, Douděra in the [[Prague derby]] received red card, after he shouted at referee Karel Rouček "Dejte třetí poločas, vy zmrdi!" ({{Lit|Give a third half, you motherfuckers!}}). Slavia chairman Jaroslav Tvrdík said that Douděra have been immediately removed from the first team and would not play for Slavia again. Douděra later apologized for his behavior.<ref>{{cite news|last=Kalas|first=Tomáš|url=https://tn.nova.cz/sport/clanek/647340-doudera-sproste-nadaval-rozhodcimu-ted-se-omlouva-chce-sam-sebe-zmenit|title=Douděra sprostě nadával rozhodčímu, teď se omlouvá. Chce sám sebe změnit|language=cs|work=[[TN.cz]]|date=10 May 2026|access-date=10 May 2026|publisher=[[TV Nova (Czech Republic)|TV Nova]]}}</ref> On 14 May 2026, Douděra was banned by the LFA Disciplinary commission for three matches.<ref>{{Cite news|first=Bartoloměj|last=Černík|title=Tresty pro trio slávistů: OSM zápasů pro Mosese, Chorý dostal šest. Co Douděra?|url=https://isport.blesk.cz/clanek/fotbal-chance-liga/475498/tresty-pro-trio-slavistu-osm-zapasu-pro-mosese-chory-dostal-sest-co-doudera.html|website=[[Blesk]]|date=14 May 2026|access-date=14 May 2026|language=cs|publisher=[[Czech News Center]]}}</ref>

==International career==
Douděra represented the Czech Republic at under-20 and under-21 level. In March 2023, he received his first call-up to the [[Czech Republic national football team|Czech senior squad]] for [[UEFA Euro 2024 qualifying Group E]] matches against [[Poland national football team|Poland]] and [[Moldova national football team|Moldova]].<ref>{{Cite news|title=Fotbalisté se sešli i s Coufalem. Ten dělá vše, aby v pátek mohl hrát|url=https://www.idnes.cz/fotbal/euro-2024/ceska-reprezentace-kvalifikace-vladimir-coufal-zdravotni-stav.A230320_155654_fot_reprez_vp2|website=[[Mladá fronta Dnes]]|location=Prague|publisher=[[Mafra (company)|Mafra]]|date=20 March 2023|access-date=21 March 2023|language=cs}}</ref> Douděra scored his first goal for the national team in November 2023 in a 3–0 victory against the latter opponent,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/czechs-stamp-ticket-euro-2024-with-3-0-win-over-10-man-moldova-2023-11-20/|title=Czechs stamp ticket to Euro 2024 with Moldova win but coach resigns|publisher=Reuters|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231121174923/https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/czechs-stamp-ticket-euro-2024-with-3-0-win-over-10-man-moldova-2023-11-20/|date=21 November 2023|archive-date=21 November 2023|access-date=30 April 2024|url-status=live}}</ref> where he also debuted.<ref>{{Cite news|first=Michal|last=Hruška|title=Kvalifikace na EURO 2024 živě: Moldavsko vs. Česko|url=https://www.fotbalzpravy.cz/rubriky/reprezentace/kvalifikace-na-euro-2024-zive-moldavsko-vs-cesko_1172.html|website=Fotbal Zprávy|date=27 March 2023|language=cs|quote=Závěrečných dvacet minut odehrál také další slávista Douděra, který si rovněž připsal svůj první reprezentační start|trans-quote=The final twenty minutes were also played by another famous player, Douděra, who also made his first international start}}</ref>

